# Design Document: Critical UX Improvements

## Overview

This design document specifies the technical implementation for four critical user experience features that address the primary adoption blockers in the AUDIRA-CHAT-AI WhatsApp Automation Platform.

The features are:

1. **Onboarding Experience** - Guided setup wizard with interactive tours and demo mode
2. **WhatsApp Connection Flow** - Simplified QR code scanning with troubleshooting
3. **Pricing & Billing Page** - Transparent pricing display and subscription management
4. **Help & Support System** - Comprehensive knowledge base with live chat and ticketing

### Design Goals

- **Reduce Time to First Value**: Enable users to send their first automated WhatsApp message within 15 minutes
- **Increase Onboarding Completion**: Achieve >80% completion rate for the onboarding wizard
- **Reduce Support Load**: Deflect 60% of support inquiries through self-service help center
- **Improve Conversion**: Increase free-to-paid conversion by 30-50%
- **Maintain Performance**: All new features must load within 3 seconds on standard connections

### Technology Stack

- **Frontend**: Next.js 14 with React 18, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- **Backend**: Node.js with Express, Prisma ORM
- **Database**: PostgreSQL (existing schema extended)
- **Payment Processing**: Stripe API
- **WhatsApp Integration**: Baileys library (existing)
- **Video Hosting**: YouTube embedded player
- **Live Chat**: Intercom SDK or custom WebSocket implementation
- **Email**: SendGrid API (existing)
- **State Management**: Zustand for client-side state
- **UI Components**: Existing brutal design system components

## Architecture

### High-Level Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Client Layer"
        A[Next.js Frontend]
        B[Onboarding Wizard]
        C[Billing Dashboard]
        D[Help Center]
        E[WhatsApp Connection UI]
    end

    subgraph "API Layer"
        F[Express API Server]
        G[Onboarding Service]
        H[Billing Service]
        I[Support Service]
        J[WhatsApp Service]
    end

    subgraph "External Services"
        K[Stripe API]
        L[SendGrid]
        M[Intercom/WebSocket]
        N[YouTube API]
    end

    subgraph "Data Layer"
        O[(PostgreSQL)]
        P[Redis Cache]
    end

    A --> F
    B --> G
    C --> H
    D --> I
    E --> J

    G --> O
    H --> K
    H --> O
    I --> O
    I --> M
    J --> O

    F --> L
    F --> P
    D --> N
```

### Component Architecture

The system follows a modular architecture with clear separation of concerns:

1. **Presentation Layer** (Next.js pages and components)
2. **Business Logic Layer** (API routes and services)
3. **Data Access Layer** (Prisma models and repositories)
4. **External Integration Layer** (Third-party service adapters)


## Components and Interfaces

### 1. Onboarding Experience Components

#### 1.1 Onboarding Wizard Component

**Location**: pps/web/src/components/onboarding/OnboardingWizard.tsx

**Purpose**: Multi-step wizard that guides new users through initial platform setup.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface OnboardingWizardProps {
  userId: string;
  tenantId: string;
  onComplete: () => void;
  onSkip: () => void;
}
```

**State Management**:
```typescript
interface OnboardingState {
  currentStep: number; // 1-5
  completedSteps: number[];
  canProceed: boolean;
  isLoading: boolean;
  demoModeEnabled: boolean;
}
```

**Steps**:
1. **Welcome & Overview** - Introduction to platform capabilities
2. **WhatsApp Connection** - Connect WhatsApp account via QR code
3. **Quick Win: Send Test Message** - Send first automated message
4. **Quick Win: Create Auto-Reply** - Set up simple auto-reply rule
5. **Completion & Next Steps** - Summary and dashboard tour invitation

**API Endpoints**:
- GET /api/onboarding/status - Get current onboarding progress
- POST /api/onboarding/step/:stepNumber/complete - Mark step as complete
- POST /api/onboarding/skip - Skip onboarding wizard
- POST /api/onboarding/resume - Resume incomplete onboarding

#### 1.2 Product Tour Component

**Location**: pps/web/src/components/onboarding/ProductTour.tsx

**Purpose**: Interactive overlay tour highlighting key platform features.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface ProductTourProps {
  isActive: boolean;
  onComplete: () => void;
  onSkip: () => void;
  startStep?: number;
}
```

**Tour Steps** (8 features):
1. Dashboard overview
2. Contacts management
3. Conversations view
4. Workflow builder
5. Analytics dashboard
6. Settings panel
7. WhatsApp connection status
8. Help center access

**Implementation**: Use 
eact-joyride library for tour functionality

**API Endpoints**:
- POST /api/onboarding/tour/complete - Record tour completion
- GET /api/onboarding/tour/status - Check if user completed tour

#### 1.3 Demo Mode Component

**Location**: pps/web/src/components/onboarding/DemoMode.tsx

**Purpose**: Sandbox environment with sample data for exploration.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface DemoModeProps {
  tenantId: string;
  onActivate: () => void;
  onDeactivate: () => void;
}
```

**Sample Data**:
- 20 sample contacts with realistic names and phone numbers
- 10 sample conversations with message history
- 3 sample workflows (welcome message, FAQ auto-reply, business hours response)

**API Endpoints**:
- POST /api/demo/activate - Enable demo mode and create sample data
- POST /api/demo/deactivate - Disable demo mode and remove sample data
- GET /api/demo/status - Check if demo mode is active

#### 1.4 Onboarding Progress Widget

**Location**: pps/web/src/components/dashboard/OnboardingProgress.tsx

**Purpose**: Dashboard widget showing setup completion status.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface OnboardingProgressProps {
  userId: string;
  tenantId: string;
}
```

**Progress Metrics**:
- Onboarding wizard completed (25%)
- WhatsApp connected (25%)
- First message sent (25%)
- First workflow created (15%)
- Team member invited (10%)

**API Endpoints**:
- GET /api/onboarding/progress - Get detailed progress breakdown

### 2. WhatsApp Connection Flow Components

#### 2.1 QR Code Scanner Interface

**Location**: pps/web/src/components/whatsapp/QRCodeScanner.tsx

**Purpose**: Display QR code for WhatsApp connection with status updates.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface QRCodeScannerProps {
  sessionId: string;
  onSuccess: (session: WhatsAppSession) => void;
  onError: (error: Error) => void;
}
```

**State Management**:
```typescript
interface QRCodeState {
  qrCode: string | null;
  expiresAt: Date | null;
  status: 'GENERATING' | 'READY' | 'SCANNING' | 'CONNECTED' | 'EXPIRED' | 'ERROR';
  countdown: number; // seconds remaining
}
```

**Features**:
- Auto-refresh QR code on expiration (every 60 seconds)
- Real-time status updates via WebSocket
- Countdown timer display
- Manual refresh button
- Connection guide sidebar

**API Endpoints**:
- POST /api/whatsapp/qr/generate - Generate new QR code
- GET /api/whatsapp/qr/:sessionId - Get current QR code
- WS /api/whatsapp/status - WebSocket for real-time status updates

#### 2.2 Connection Status Indicator

**Location**: pps/web/src/components/whatsapp/ConnectionStatus.tsx

**Purpose**: Display current WhatsApp connection status across the application.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface ConnectionStatusProps {
  sessionId: string;
  variant: 'badge' | 'detailed' | 'navbar';
}
```

**Status Types**:
- CONNECTED - Green indicator, "Connected"
- CONNECTING - Yellow indicator, "Connecting..."
- DISCONNECTED - Red indicator, "Disconnected"
- BANNED - Gray indicator, "Account Banned"

**Display Locations**:
- Navigation bar (all pages)
- Dashboard widget
- WhatsApp settings page

**API Endpoints**:
- GET /api/whatsapp/status/:sessionId - Get current connection status

#### 2.3 Troubleshooting Wizard

**Location**: pps/web/src/components/whatsapp/TroubleshootingWizard.tsx

**Purpose**: Guided diagnostic tool for resolving connection issues.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface TroubleshootingWizardProps {
  sessionId: string;
  onResolved: () => void;
  onCreateTicket: (diagnostics: DiagnosticData) => void;
}
```

**Diagnostic Checks**:
1. Internet connectivity test
2. WhatsApp service availability check
3. Session validity verification
4. Phone number format validation
5. Multi-device limit check

**Resolution Steps**:
- Regenerate QR code
- Clear session and reconnect
- Check WhatsApp app version
- Verify phone number
- Contact support with diagnostics

**API Endpoints**:
- POST /api/whatsapp/troubleshoot - Run diagnostic tests
- POST /api/whatsapp/session/reset - Reset session for reconnection

#### 2.4 Session Management UI

**Location**: pps/web/src/components/whatsapp/SessionManagement.tsx

**Purpose**: View and manage all WhatsApp sessions for a tenant.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface SessionManagementProps {
  tenantId: string;
}
```

**Session Display**:
```typescript
interface SessionDisplay {
  id: string;
  phoneNumber: string;
  status: ConnectionStatus;
  connectedAt: Date;
  lastActivity: Date;
  deviceInfo: string;
}
```

**Actions**:
- View session details
- Disconnect session
- Reconnect session
- Delete session

**API Endpoints**:
- GET /api/whatsapp/sessions - List all sessions for tenant
- DELETE /api/whatsapp/sessions/:sessionId - Disconnect and remove session
- POST /api/whatsapp/sessions/:sessionId/reconnect - Initiate reconnection

#### 2.5 Auto-Reconnect Handler

**Location**: pps/web/src/services/whatsapp/AutoReconnectService.ts

**Purpose**: Background service that automatically attempts to reconnect dropped sessions.

**Configuration**:
```typescript
interface AutoReconnectConfig {
  enabled: boolean;
  maxAttempts: 5;
  backoffSchedule: [30, 60, 120, 240, 480]; // seconds
  notifyOnFailure: boolean;
}
```

**Behavior**:
1. Detect disconnection event
2. Wait for backoff period
3. Attempt reconnection
4. Retry with exponential backoff
5. Notify user after all attempts fail

**API Endpoints**:
- POST /api/whatsapp/reconnect/:sessionId - Trigger reconnection attempt
- GET /api/whatsapp/reconnect/status/:sessionId - Get reconnection status

### 3. Pricing & Billing Components

#### 3.1 Public Pricing Page

**Location**: pps/web/src/app/(public)/pricing/page.tsx

**Purpose**: Public-facing page displaying all pricing tiers and features.

**Pricing Tiers**:
```typescript
interface PricingTier {
  id: 'FREE' | 'STARTER' | 'PROFESSIONAL' | 'ENTERPRISE';
  name: string;
  monthlyPrice: number;
  annualPrice: number;
  annualDiscount: number; // percentage
  features: string[];
  limits: {
    messages: number;
    contacts: number;
    workflows: number;
    teamMembers: number;
  };
  cta: string;
  popular?: boolean;
}
```

**Features**:
- Responsive grid layout (1-4 columns based on screen size)
- Annual/monthly toggle
- Feature comparison table
- Highlighted "most popular" tier
- Clear CTAs for each tier

**API Endpoints**:
- GET /api/pricing/tiers - Get all pricing tier information
- GET /api/pricing/features - Get feature comparison data

#### 3.2 Feature Comparison Table

**Location**: pps/web/src/components/pricing/FeatureComparison.tsx

**Purpose**: Detailed comparison of features across all pricing tiers.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface FeatureComparisonProps {
  tiers: PricingTier[];
  categories: FeatureCategory[];
}

interface FeatureCategory {
  name: string;
  features: Feature[];
}

interface Feature {
  name: string;
  description: string;
  availability: {
    [tierId: string]: boolean | string | number;
  };
}
```

**Categories**:
- Core Features
- Automation & Workflows
- Team Collaboration
- Analytics & Reporting
- Integrations
- Support & SLA

**Features**:
- Sticky header on scroll
- Sortable by category
- Tooltip explanations
- Mobile-responsive (horizontal scroll)

#### 3.3 Billing Dashboard

**Location**: pps/web/src/app/(dashboard)/settings/billing/page.tsx

**Purpose**: Manage subscription, payment methods, and view billing history.

**Sections**:
1. **Current Plan** - Active tier, next billing date, amount
2. **Usage Metrics** - Current usage vs. limits with progress bars
3. **Payment Methods** - Manage credit cards
4. **Billing History** - Invoice list with download links
5. **Plan Management** - Upgrade/downgrade options

**API Endpoints**:
- GET /api/billing/subscription - Get current subscription details
- GET /api/billing/usage - Get current usage statistics
- GET /api/billing/invoices - List all invoices
- GET /api/billing/invoices/:id/download - Download invoice PDF

#### 3.4 Usage Quota Display

**Location**: pps/web/src/components/billing/UsageQuota.tsx

**Purpose**: Visual display of resource usage against plan limits.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface UsageQuotaProps {
  tenantId: string;
  variant: 'dashboard' | 'detailed' | 'warning';
}

interface UsageData {
  messages: { used: number; limit: number; };
  contacts: { used: number; limit: number; };
  workflows: { used: number; limit: number; };
  teamMembers: { used: number; limit: number; };
}
```

**Warning Thresholds**:
- 80% - Yellow warning notification
- 90% - Orange alert with upgrade suggestion
- 100% - Red blocking modal with upgrade requirement

**API Endpoints**:
- GET /api/billing/usage/current - Get real-time usage data
- GET /api/billing/usage/history - Get historical usage trends

#### 3.5 Upgrade/Downgrade Flow

**Location**: pps/web/src/components/billing/PlanChangeFlow.tsx

**Purpose**: Guided flow for changing subscription tiers.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface PlanChangeFlowProps {
  currentTier: PricingTier;
  targetTier: PricingTier;
  type: 'upgrade' | 'downgrade';
  onComplete: () => void;
  onCancel: () => void;
}
```

**Upgrade Flow Steps**:
1. Select new tier
2. Review feature changes
3. Calculate prorated charges
4. Confirm payment
5. Activate new features

**Downgrade Flow Steps**:
1. Select lower tier
2. Review feature losses
3. Check usage compatibility
4. Schedule for end of billing cycle
5. Confirm downgrade

**API Endpoints**:
- POST /api/billing/upgrade - Process immediate upgrade
- POST /api/billing/downgrade - Schedule end-of-cycle downgrade
- POST /api/billing/calculate-proration - Calculate prorated charges

#### 3.6 Payment Method Management

**Location**: pps/web/src/components/billing/PaymentMethods.tsx

**Purpose**: Add, update, and remove payment methods.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface PaymentMethodsProps {
  tenantId: string;
}

interface PaymentMethod {
  id: string;
  type: 'card';
  brand: string; // visa, mastercard, amex
  last4: string;
  expiryMonth: number;
  expiryYear: number;
  isDefault: boolean;
}
```

**Features**:
- Stripe Elements integration for secure card input
- PCI-DSS compliant tokenization
- Set default payment method
- Expiration warnings (30 days before)
- Delete non-default methods

**API Endpoints**:
- GET /api/billing/payment-methods - List all payment methods
- POST /api/billing/payment-methods - Add new payment method
- PUT /api/billing/payment-methods/:id/default - Set as default
- DELETE /api/billing/payment-methods/:id - Remove payment method

### 4. Help & Support Components

#### 4.1 Help Center

**Location**: pps/web/src/app/(public)/help/page.tsx

**Purpose**: Comprehensive knowledge base with articles, FAQs, and videos.

**Structure**:
```typescript
interface HelpCenterStructure {
  categories: Category[];
  popularArticles: Article[];
  recentArticles: Article[];
}

interface Category {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  icon: string;
  articleCount: number;
  subcategories?: Category[];
}

interface Article {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  slug: string;
  categoryId: string;
  content: string; // Markdown
  author: string;
  publishedAt: Date;
  updatedAt: Date;
  views: number;
  helpfulCount: number;
  relatedArticles: string[]; // article IDs
  videoUrl?: string;
}
```

**Categories**:
1. Getting Started
2. WhatsApp Connection
3. Contacts & Conversations
4. Workflows & Automation
5. Billing & Subscriptions
6. Team Management
7. Integrations
8. Troubleshooting

**API Endpoints**:
- GET /api/help/categories - List all categories
- GET /api/help/articles - List articles (with filters)
- GET /api/help/articles/:slug - Get article by slug
- POST /api/help/articles/:id/helpful - Mark article as helpful
- POST /api/help/articles/:id/view - Increment view count

#### 4.2 Search Functionality

**Location**: pps/web/src/components/help/HelpSearch.tsx

**Purpose**: Full-text search across all help content.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface HelpSearchProps {
  placeholder?: string;
  onResultSelect?: (result: SearchResult) => void;
}

interface SearchResult {
  type: 'article' | 'faq' | 'video';
  id: string;
  title: string;
  excerpt: string;
  url: string;
  relevance: number;
}
```

**Features**:
- Real-time search as user types (debounced)
- Fuzzy matching for typos
- Highlighted search terms in results
- Category filtering
- Recent searches history
- "No results" with support ticket option

**API Endpoints**:
- GET /api/help/search?q={query} - Search all help content
- GET /api/help/search/suggestions?q={query} - Get autocomplete suggestions

#### 4.3 FAQ Component

**Location**: pps/web/src/components/help/FAQ.tsx

**Purpose**: Accordion-style frequently asked questions.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface FAQProps {
  category?: string;
  limit?: number;
}

interface FAQItem {
  id: string;
  question: string;
  answer: string; // Markdown
  category: string;
  order: number;
  helpfulCount: number;
}
```

**Categories**:
- Getting Started
- Billing
- WhatsApp Connection
- Features
- Troubleshooting

**Features**:
- Expand/collapse individual items
- "Was this helpful?" feedback
- Link to related articles
- Print-friendly format

**API Endpoints**:
- GET /api/help/faq - Get all FAQ items
- POST /api/help/faq/:id/helpful - Mark FAQ as helpful

#### 4.4 Live Chat Widget

**Location**: pps/web/src/components/support/LiveChat.tsx

**Purpose**: Real-time chat with support agents.

**Props Interface**:
```typescript
interface LiveChatProps {
  userId: string;
  tenantId: string;
  initialMessage?: string;
}

interface ChatMessage {
  id: string;
  senderId: string;
  senderType: 'user' | 'agent' | 'bot';
  content: string;
  timestamp: Date;
  attachments?: Attachment[];
}

interface Attachment {
  id: string;
  filename: string;
  url: string;
  size: number;
  mimeType: string;
}
```

**Features**:
- Floating widget (bottom-right corner)
- Minimize/maximize
- Typing indicators
- File attachments (up to 10MB)
- Conversation history
- Estimated wait time
- Offline mode (creates ticket instead)
- Email transcript on close

**Implementation Options**:
1. **Intercom SDK** (recommended for quick implementation)
2. **Custom WebSocket** (for full control)

**API Endpoints** (if custom):
- WS /api/support/chat - WebSocket connection
- POST /api/support/chat/messages - Send message
- POST /api/support/chat/attachments - Upload file
- GET /api/support/chat/history - Get conversation history
- POST /api/support/chat/transcript - Email transcript

#### 4.5 Support Ticket System

**Location**: pps/web/src/app/(dashboard)/support/tickets/page.tsx

**Purpose**: Submit and track support tickets.

**Ticket Interface**:
```typescript
interface SupportTicket {
  id: string;
  ticketNumber: string; // e.g., "TICKET-12345"
  userId: string;
  tenantId: string;
  category: TicketCategory;
  priority: 'low' | 'medium' | 'high' | 'urgent';
  status: 'open' | 'in_progress' | 'waiting_on_customer' | 'resolved' | 'closed';
  subject: string;
  description: string;
  attachments: Attachment[];
  createdAt: Date;
  updatedAt: Date;
  resolvedAt?: Date;
  assignedTo?: string; // agent ID
  messages: TicketMessage[];
}

interface TicketMessage {
  id: string;
  ticketId: string;
  senderId: string;
  senderType: 'user' | 'agent';
  content: string;
  timestamp: Date;
  attachments?: Attachment[];
}

type TicketCategory = 
  | 'technical_issue'
  | 'billing_question'
  | 'feature_request'
  | 'account_management'
  | 'whatsapp_connection'
  | 'other';
```

**Features**:
- Create new ticket with form
- View all tickets (list and detail views)
- Reply to tickets
- Upload attachments
- Email notifications on status changes
- Filter by status and category
- Search tickets

**API Endpoints**:
- POST /api/support/tickets - Create new ticket
- GET /api/support/tickets - List user's tickets
- GET /api/support/tickets/:id - Get ticket details
- POST /api/support/tickets/:id/messages - Add message to ticket
- PUT /api/support/tickets/:id/status - Update ticket status (agent only)

#### 4.6 Video Tutorial Library

**Location**: pps/web/src/app/(public)/help/videos/page.tsx

**Purpose**: Curated library of instructional videos.

**Video Interface**:
```typescript
interface VideoTutorial {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  description: string;
  youtubeId: string;
  duration: number; // seconds
  category: string;
  tags: string[];
  thumbnail: string;
  publishedAt: Date;
  views: number;
  transcript?: string;
}
```

**Features**:
- Grid layout with thumbnails
- Category filtering
- Search by title/description
- Embedded YouTube player
- Playback speed controls
- Closed captions
- Track watch progress
- Related videos

**API Endpoints**:
- GET /api/help/videos - List all videos
- GET /api/help/videos/:id - Get video details
- POST /api/help/videos/:id/view - Increment view count
- POST /api/help/videos/:id/progress - Save watch progress

#### 4.7 Status Page

**Location**: pps/web/src/app/(public)/status/page.tsx

**Purpose**: Public page showing platform operational status.

**Status Interface**:
```typescript
interface ServiceStatus {
  service: string;
  status: 'operational' | 'degraded' | 'partial_outage' | 'major_outage';
  lastChecked: Date;
}

interface Incident {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  description: string;
  status: 'investigating' | 'identified' | 'monitoring' | 'resolved';
  severity: 'minor' | 'major' | 'critical';
  affectedServices: string[];
  createdAt: Date;
  updatedAt: Date;
  resolvedAt?: Date;
  updates: IncidentUpdate[];
}

interface IncidentUpdate {
  id: string;
  message: string;
  timestamp: Date;
}

interface UptimeMetric {
  service: string;
  period: '30d' | '60d' | '90d';
  uptime: number; // percentage
}
```

**Services Monitored**:
- API Server
- WhatsApp Connection Service
- Dashboard/Web App
- Database
- Email Service

**Features**:
- Real-time status indicators
- Incident history (12 months)
- Uptime metrics (30/60/90 days)
- Subscribe to status updates (email/SMS)
- RSS feed
- Historical incident timeline

**API Endpoints**:
- GET /api/status/current - Get current status of all services
- GET /api/status/incidents - List recent incidents
- GET /api/status/uptime - Get uptime metrics
- POST /api/status/subscribe - Subscribe to status updates

#### 4.8 Contact Form

**Location**: pps/web/src/app/(public)/contact/page.tsx

**Purpose**: General inquiry form for non-technical questions.

**Form Interface**:
```typescript
interface ContactFormData {
  name: string;
  email: string;
  subject: string;
  inquiryType: 'sales' | 'partnership' | 'feedback' | 'other';
  message: string;
  captchaToken: string;
}
```

**Features**:
- Form validation
- reCAPTCHA v3 integration
- Auto-response email
- Route to appropriate team
- 24-hour response SLA

**API Endpoints**:
- POST /api/contact - Submit contact form


## Data Models

### Database Schema Extensions

The following models extend the existing Prisma schema to support the new features.

#### OnboardingProgress Model

```prisma
model OnboardingProgress {
  id                    String   @id @default(cuid())
  userId                String   @unique
  tenantId              String

  // Wizard completion
  wizardCompleted       Boolean  @default(false)
  wizardCompletedAt     DateTime?
  currentStep           Int      @default(1)
  completedSteps        Int[]    @default([])
  skipped               Boolean  @default(false)

  // Product tour
  tourCompleted         Boolean  @default(false)
  tourCompletedAt       DateTime?
  tourStep              Int      @default(0)

  // Demo mode
  demoModeActive        Boolean  @default(false)
  demoModeActivatedAt   DateTime?

  // Progress metrics
  whatsappConnected     Boolean  @default(false)
  firstMessageSent      Boolean  @default(false)
  firstWorkflowCreated  Boolean  @default(false)
  teamMemberInvited     Boolean  @default(false)

  // Timestamps
  createdAt             DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt             DateTime @updatedAt

  // Relations
  user                  User     @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  tenant                Tenant   @relation(fields: [tenantId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)

  @@index([userId])
  @@index([tenantId])
}
```

#### Subscription Model

```prisma
model Subscription {
  id                    String   @id @default(cuid())
  tenantId              String   @unique

  // Plan details
  tier                  String   // FREE, STARTER, PROFESSIONAL, ENTERPRISE
  status                String   @default("active") // active, past_due, canceled, trialing

  // Billing
  billingCycle          String   @default("monthly") // monthly, annual
  currentPeriodStart    DateTime
  currentPeriodEnd      DateTime
  cancelAtPeriodEnd     Boolean  @default(false)

  // Stripe integration
  stripeCustomerId      String?  @unique
  stripeSubscriptionId  String?  @unique
